TITLE: 'It's always on my mind': Five years since the Parkland massacre, survivors' pain is fresh
SUMMARY: Here's what three survivors want Americans to know nearly five years since a gunman killed 17 people at their high school in Parkland, Florida.<div class="fbz_enclosure" style="clear: left;">

TITLE: On Parkland fifth anniversary, gun safety advocates cite 'less progress' than expected
SUMMARY: After the 2018 Parkland, Florida, high school shooting, the initial goal was to reduce gun violence by 25% by 2025. Gun violence has gone up nationwide.<div class="fbz_enclosure" style="clear: left;">

TITLE: She's giving Valentine's Day flowers to 800 widows to 'show love to those who are hurting'
SUMMARY: Ashley Manning is founder of the Valentine's Day Widow Outreach Project, a program she said she created  "to show love to those who are hurting."<div class="fbz_enclosure" style="clear: left;">

TITLE: Ukrainian soldiers call for more Western weapons
SUMMARY: As Russia increases its attacks in Ukraine's south and east, soldiers defending the frontline say they urgently need more ammunition and planes to win the war.<div style="clear: both; padding-top: 0.2em;">

TITLE: Three dead, five wounded in shooting at Michigan State University, suspect found dead
SUMMARY: Three people were killed at Michigan State University. The suspect was found dead from a self-inflicted gunshot wound, authorities said.<div class="fbz_enclosure" style="clear: left;">

TITLE: 3 killed, 5 injured in Michigan State University shooting rampage; gunman dead: Live updates
SUMMARY: A gunman killed three people and wounded five others on the campus of Michigan State University before taking his own life, police said.<div class="fbz_enclosure" style="clear: left;">

TITLE: Man rescued 199 hours after Turkey quake
SUMMARY: Rescuers in Turkey on Tuesday pulled a man from under the rubble almost 200 hours after the devastating earthquake. Meanwhile in Syria, efforts to help survivors were marred by the divisions from 12 years of civil war. (Feb. 14)<div style="clear: both; padding-top: 0.2em;">

TITLE: Haley expected to announce GOP presidential bid
SUMMARY: According to a person familiar with the plans but not authorized to speak about them, the former South Carolina governor Nikki Haley is planning to launch her presidential campaign at an event in Charleston on the Wednesday, February 15th. (Feb. 13)<div class="fbz_enclosure" style="clear: left;">
